12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 481, as
14 amended by Section 1, Chapter 283, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp. 2024,
15 Section 481), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 481. A State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision
17 hereinafter referred to as the "Board", is hereby re-created, to
18 continue until July 1, 2025 2030, in accordance with the provisions
19 of the Oklahoma Sunset Law. The Board shall be composed of seven
20 (7) allopathic physicians licensed to practice medicine in this
21 state and represent the public and four (4) lay members. The
22 physician members of the Board shall be graduates of legally
23 chartered medical schools recognized by the Oklahoma State Regents
24 for Higher Education or the Liaison Council on Medical Education.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1032 Page 1
1 The physician members shall have actively practiced as licensed
2 physicians continuously in this state for the three (3) years
3 immediately preceding their appointment to the Board. All members
4 of the Board shall be residents of this state and shall be appointed
5 by the Governor as provided for in Section 482 of this title. All
6 present members of the Board shall continue to serve for the
7 remainder of their current terms.
8 Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of February,

